Hi RetailGrid Finance Team,

Thanks for flagging this — I pulled the raw ingestion logs for proj_55019 for the May billing cycle. The discrepancy is because your billing count includes events submitted through the /v3/events/batch-import endpoint used during your March-to-May historical data migration, which our billing system counted as May-cycle usage rather than pro-rating them across the original event dates. This is a known limitation with the batch-import endpoint referenced in our API Documentation — it doesn't currently carry historical billing timestamps.

I've issued a billing correction crediting your account $2,340.00, which will appear on your June invoice. Going forward, large historical backfills should be flagged to your Customer Success Manager in advance so we can apply a migration billing exclusion before the import runs.

Apologies for the confusion, and thanks for catching this.

Best,
Marcus
Nimbus Analytics Support — Billing Team

